WEBVTT



00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:04.576
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.384 --> 00:00:09.824
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:15.040
Using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent,

00:00:14.752 --> 00:00:18.752
and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:27.040
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:27.008 --> 00:00:36.448
Today, we invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the Gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:38.976 --> 00:00:41.632
Peace be with you. Friends for this...

00:00:41.792 --> 00:00:49.088
23rd Sunday of Ordinary Time, we're reading from the 14th chapter of Luke, and this is very serious spiritual business.

00:00:48.736 --> 00:00:52.576
We're talking, if you want to put it this way, very high octane.

00:00:52.352 --> 00:00:53.824
Spirituality.

00:00:53.856 --> 00:00:56.544
Remember the story of the rich young man? Yeah.

00:00:56.480 --> 00:00:58.464
This young kid full of, you know,

00:00:58.624 --> 00:01:08.672
Because good spiritual enthusiasm comes to Jesus. What must I do to attain eternal life? And Jesus first speaks of the commandments. And the young guy says, you know, with confidence. And I'm moving.

00:01:08.192 --> 00:01:11.040
And I believe them. I've kept all these from my youth. Yeah.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:14.368
And then Jesus says, looking at him with love, mind you.

00:01:14.304 --> 00:01:15.328
Um,

00:01:15.296 --> 00:01:17.824
Well, are you willing to sell all you've got?

00:01:17.536 --> 00:01:20.256
And give to the poor and follow me.

00:01:20.224 --> 00:01:26.080
And the young kid went away sad because he was living the spiritual life at a decent level.

00:01:26.784 --> 00:01:29.376
But he wasn't ready for the serious stuff

00:01:29.472 --> 00:01:30.912
Think of a, um,

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:37.632
You know, a kid that's showing promise in football and the coach recognizes he plays the basics well.

00:01:37.632 --> 00:01:41.696
And then he wants to draw him into the really serious playing of the game.

00:01:41.824 --> 00:01:43.424
The physical.

00:01:43.328 --> 00:01:49.344
Demands and then the strategic thinking and all that that's required to play the game at a really high level.

00:01:49.184 --> 00:01:52.800
Or a young kid that's good at the basics of piano.

00:01:52.704 --> 00:01:57.440
And you can even master, you know, high level pop songs and a little Gershwin and, you know,

00:01:57.152 --> 00:01:59.232
The teacher goes, okay, now...

00:01:59.104 --> 00:02:02.304
Maybe you're ready for Chopin, for Beethoven, and so on.

00:02:02.688 --> 00:02:05.440
Well, there's something similar in the spiritual order.

00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:13.536
And the trouble is a lot of us sinners, we're kind of satisfied with low-level spirituality. What I mean is, we're like the rich young man.

00:02:13.248 --> 00:02:23.296
Hey, you know, I'm a decent person. I'm not killing people and I'm not stealing and I'm not committing adultery and I don't lie too often.

00:02:22.816 --> 00:02:28.256
You know, I'm following the commandments. I go to Mass, you know, pretty regularly. Yeah.

00:02:28.448 --> 00:02:37.568
Well, great. You know, great. Nothing wrong with that because the commandments are the basic level, if you want. It's the rudiments of the spiritual life.

00:02:38.848 --> 00:02:40.928
But when the church gives this

00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:44.640
This challenge, it's born of Jesus, of course. This challenge, this challenge.

00:02:45.024 --> 00:02:47.520
To live it really seriously.

00:02:47.552 --> 00:02:52.032
To move into the upper levels of the spiritual life. Most of us

00:02:51.744 --> 00:02:52.768
Bark.

00:02:53.088 --> 00:02:56.288
Not ready for that. It's a little too much.

00:02:56.608 --> 00:02:57.632
will.

00:02:57.440 --> 00:03:01.024
With that in mind, look at this extraordinary reading.

00:03:01.152 --> 00:03:02.048
And,

00:03:01.792 --> 00:03:03.680
Let me say this at the outset.

00:03:03.456 --> 00:03:05.952
1.

00:03:05.632 --> 00:03:07.616
To domesticate this.

00:03:07.808 --> 00:03:10.880
Or think it away or it's always just symbolic talk.

00:03:10.688 --> 00:03:12.064
Listen to Jesus now.

00:03:12.992 --> 00:03:14.976
If anyone comes to me

00:03:15.648 --> 00:03:16.672
without

00:03:16.544 --> 00:03:18.528
hating his father and mother.

00:03:18.944 --> 00:03:20.448
wife and children

00:03:20.448 --> 00:03:22.080
Brothers and sisters,

00:03:21.984 --> 00:03:24.256
Even his own life

00:03:24.736 --> 00:03:27.136
He cannot be my disciple.

00:03:27.904 --> 00:03:31.104
Okay, now put yourself in this

00:03:31.136 --> 00:03:41.152
place, the crowd hearing this from Jesus. They recognize him. Sure, he's a rabbi, he's a spiritual teacher, he's a miracle worker, and they're very intrigued by him.

00:03:41.504 --> 00:03:43.424
But then he lays out

00:03:43.360 --> 00:03:47.168
To use Bonhoeffer's terms here, the cost of discipleship.

00:03:48.064 --> 00:03:51.104
If anyone comes to me and wants to be my disciple, I'm going to die

00:03:51.584 --> 00:03:54.336
Without heeding father and mother

00:03:54.432 --> 00:03:55.968
Wife and children

00:03:55.936 --> 00:03:57.504
Brothers and sisters,

00:03:57.248 --> 00:03:58.912
Even his own life.

00:03:58.976 --> 00:04:00.832
He cannot be my disciple.

00:04:01.184 --> 00:04:11.232
Now, look, I know I've heard a hundred sermons on this and have read the relevant text that will stress that in Jesus' Aramaic, this language of like hate and love,

00:04:10.752 --> 00:04:15.040
It was not so much of either or. It was a sense of prioritization. Yeah.

00:04:14.848 --> 00:04:17.760
Okay, there's truth enough to that.

00:04:17.952 --> 00:04:20.256
But see, I don't want us.

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:24.000
To to soften this language too much

00:04:23.936 --> 00:04:27.680
This is meant to be a kind of shock therapy.

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:35.840
You're taking discipleship seriously? Well, here's what it entails. Now, let me try to parse this out.

00:04:35.584 --> 00:04:36.384
For you.

00:04:36.640 --> 00:04:38.016
I think there's a,

00:04:38.304 --> 00:04:41.984
A more positive and a more negative way maybe we could assess this

00:04:42.944 --> 00:04:44.000
First of all,

00:04:44.832 --> 00:04:46.976
Do we sinners have the tendency?

00:04:47.392 --> 00:04:48.608
To make

00:04:48.416 --> 00:04:50.912
Of very good things

00:04:51.552 --> 00:04:52.928
The ultimate good.

00:04:54.016 --> 00:04:56.256
No, I mean father and mother.

00:04:56.192 --> 00:04:57.568
Wife and children

00:04:57.600 --> 00:04:59.072
Brothers and sisters,

00:04:58.944 --> 00:05:01.024
good things. well of course.

00:05:01.248 --> 00:05:06.656
And the Society of Jesus, the Jewish Society of the First Century, very family-centric.

00:05:06.272 --> 00:05:07.328
Uh,

00:05:07.104 --> 00:05:08.096
Culture.

00:05:08.608 --> 00:05:12.160
Are these good relationships? Of course they are. Of course they are.

00:05:13.536 --> 00:05:14.912
However,,

00:05:15.648 --> 00:05:17.696
They're not the supreme good.

00:05:19.584 --> 00:05:21.504
The Sumum Bonum.

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:24.064
Only God

00:05:24.256 --> 00:05:25.792
is the supreme good.

00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:33.024
What's the first commandment? You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, all your soul, all your mind, all your strength, all your

00:05:35.392 --> 00:05:37.056
Who comes first?

00:05:37.120 --> 00:05:40.128
See, and this is where everybody, it gets challenging.

00:05:40.224 --> 00:05:41.984
Who comes first?

00:05:41.888 --> 00:05:43.424
It can't be my mother.

00:05:44.384 --> 00:05:46.080
it can't be my father.

00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:48.800
It can't be my brothers or sisters.

00:05:49.408 --> 00:05:50.464
And,

00:05:50.304 --> 00:05:54.208
It can't even be my own life that comes first.

00:05:55.392 --> 00:05:57.088
God must come first.

00:05:57.504 --> 00:06:00.512
So what if God's making a demand?

00:06:00.512 --> 00:06:03.520
That's at odds with what my father and mother want.

00:06:04.672 --> 00:06:06.304
God is the supreme good.

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:11.392
God makes a demand in my life that means I'm alienated from my brothers and sisters.

00:06:11.104 --> 00:06:12.352
Okay

00:06:12.832 --> 00:06:13.824
Press it.

00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:16.448
God makes a demand.

00:06:16.992 --> 00:06:20.160
that requires that I surrender my life

00:06:20.768 --> 00:06:21.728
Now,

00:06:21.984 --> 00:06:23.360
All the martyrs.

00:06:23.648 --> 00:06:25.088
All the great martyrs.

00:06:25.024 --> 00:06:27.104
Faced exactly that.

00:06:26.880 --> 00:06:27.872
Decision.

00:06:29.376 --> 00:06:31.008
What do you decide?

00:06:31.744 --> 00:06:35.264
Oh, I hope I never come to that. Yeah, I know. I know. We all do.

00:06:35.936 --> 00:06:37.312
But if you did,

00:06:38.368 --> 00:06:39.936
what would you decide?

00:06:41.312 --> 00:06:46.432
Unless you hate your mother and father. See, interpret that as unless you are a mother and father.

00:06:46.528 --> 00:06:52.096
able to put your mother and father second to the demand of God.

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:54.304
You can't be my disciple.

00:06:55.072 --> 00:07:01.024
Okay. Unless you put your love for your brother and sister second to your love for God. Okay.

00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:04.928
You can if you're my disciple. Now, think about the parent.

00:07:05.024 --> 00:07:06.208
Unless,

00:07:06.368 --> 00:07:09.056
You can put your love for your child

00:07:09.472 --> 00:07:14.720
Second, to your love for God. Now revisit that awful story.

00:07:14.528 --> 00:07:16.448
in the book of Genesis.

00:07:16.288 --> 00:07:18.464
When God says to Abraham,

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:27.680
You know, Isaac, your beloved, your son, Isaac, the son of the promise. You know, Isaac, whom you love. I want you to sacrifice him to me.

00:07:27.936 --> 00:07:33.216
Is it God being cruel? No, it's the same lesson. It's the same lesson.

00:07:33.216 --> 00:07:35.872
A spiritual exercise if you want.

00:07:35.936 --> 00:07:41.312
Do you love me more than you love even your beloved child?

00:07:41.664 --> 00:07:43.744
Unless that's the case.

00:07:43.776 --> 00:07:46.848
You're not ready to be my follower.

00:07:47.168 --> 00:07:51.136
You see what I mean everybody when I say this is high octane stuff.

00:07:51.328 --> 00:07:54.400
This is for the very spiritually serious.

00:07:54.144 --> 00:07:57.888
Now, I said there were two levels. That's a more positive one.

00:07:57.696 --> 00:08:00.928
But now move it to that second more negative level.

00:08:00.736 --> 00:08:04.864
And keep in mind what I mentioned to you last Sunday about pride.

00:08:05.376 --> 00:08:09.600
So, first thing is, can I put God above?

00:08:09.504 --> 00:08:11.200
Even these highest goods.

00:08:12.416 --> 00:08:14.784
But can I also recognize

00:08:15.168 --> 00:08:17.440
The ways that pride

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:21.824
Has perverted and twisted all of these relationships.

00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:25.440
Out of self-regard

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:30.400
I mean, can I start using my mother and father for my own benefit?

00:08:30.400 --> 00:08:35.296
Can I manipulate them as part of my scheme of life?

00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:41.152
Or think of parents that live vicariously in an manipulative way through their children.

00:08:42.112 --> 00:08:47.712
My brothers and sisters, do I involve them in my own kind of prideful, egotistic games?

00:08:49.248 --> 00:08:50.880
Can you see how everybody

00:08:50.912 --> 00:08:53.760
In the measure that we do all that,

00:08:54.400 --> 00:08:57.280
We should hate these relationships.

00:08:57.600 --> 00:09:04.032
See, I'm not saying in themselves are bad. I'm saying in the measure that they've been twisted by pride, right?

00:09:05.376 --> 00:09:09.024
They become spiritually toxic.

00:09:10.048 --> 00:09:11.744
I should hate them.

00:09:12.576 --> 00:09:14.368
I should repudiate them.

00:09:15.296 --> 00:09:20.288
See, very often in the spiritual order, people, they're enthusiastic about following the Lord.

00:09:21.056 --> 00:09:23.616
But they're not willing to let go.

00:09:23.520 --> 00:09:27.040
Of the twisted, weird parts of their life.

00:09:27.456 --> 00:09:34.816
They're not willing to let go of the of the prideful way that I manipulated and abused people around me.

00:09:34.752 --> 00:09:36.352
I don't want to let go of that.

00:09:37.344 --> 00:09:38.688
Again, I'm using...

00:09:38.528 --> 00:09:40.992
a dumb example, but it always helps me to

00:09:40.768 --> 00:09:42.912
So if you're learning something,

00:09:42.688 --> 00:09:44.640
The proper golf swing

00:09:44.576 --> 00:09:50.112
Well, all of us bad golfers have this bad swing in place. We're doing it the wrong way.

00:09:49.984 --> 00:09:52.480
Everything about our swing is off.

00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:54.944
You have to hate that swing.

00:09:54.720 --> 00:10:04.768
Right. You have to hate it. You have to repudiate it. You can't make compromises with it. Like, well, I'll try to fit a little bit of that into my... No, no. That's a bad swing. Right.

00:10:04.288 --> 00:10:13.504
It's been serving you very poorly all these years, and you've got to go through the painful transition to a whole new way of striking the ball.

00:10:15.488 --> 00:10:20.992
And compromising, playing games. I'll do a little bit of this, a little bit of that. It's not going to work, right?

00:10:21.408 --> 00:10:24.192
Do you see how you have to hate people?

00:10:23.968 --> 00:10:28.160
The ways that your relationships and your style has

00:10:28.608 --> 00:10:30.624
Crippled you spiritually.

00:10:31.264 --> 00:10:32.672
If you're not,

00:10:32.512 --> 00:10:38.336
You're not ready for the Lord Jesus. You're not ready for real discipleship.

00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:40.896
This is, you know, in the Old Testament terminology,

00:10:41.216 --> 00:10:45.312
Israel hankering for the flesh parts of Egypt, right?

00:10:45.024 --> 00:10:47.840
Oh, if only we were back in Egypt.

00:10:48.128 --> 00:10:53.408
even though we were slaves in Egypt. But, oh, if only we were back there, we had enough to eat.

00:10:53.344 --> 00:10:57.888
Yeah. Come on, you're not ready for the promised land if that's the way you're thinking. Yeah.

00:10:57.792 --> 00:11:07.584
you know oh let me go back to these old manipulative habits and these old prideful ways that i i related to people around me. no no you have to hate.

00:11:07.424 --> 00:11:09.600
you have to hate all of that.

00:11:09.824 --> 00:11:11.328
If you're

00:11:11.104 --> 00:11:13.344
willing to follow the Lord Jesus.

00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:15.232
Now, look how he sums this up.

00:11:16.416 --> 00:11:18.784
Whoever does not carry

00:11:18.528 --> 00:11:20.960
His own cross.

00:11:21.504 --> 00:11:23.296
And come after me.

00:11:23.168 --> 00:11:25.152
cannot be my disciple.

00:11:26.336 --> 00:11:32.800
Hey, hey, hey. I know. I know. Look, I'm a sinner. You're sinners. And so this is a really hard talk.

00:11:33.152 --> 00:11:38.144
They, they knew about crosses, carrying the cross, what the cross meant.

00:11:38.848 --> 00:11:43.968
And we hold it up in front of us all the time, the cross of Jesus. What does it mean?

00:11:43.904 --> 00:11:45.152
It means,

00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.744
I'm I'm stripped of wealth

00:11:47.584 --> 00:11:56.576
I'm stripped of pleasure. I'm stripped of power. I'm stripped of honor. Of all these things that my prideful self wants,

00:11:56.864 --> 00:12:00.832
I'm stripped of all these things. Listen.

00:12:00.928 --> 00:12:03.872
That I have tended to make

00:12:03.904 --> 00:12:06.528
Into absolute goods

00:12:07.424 --> 00:12:08.288
Right?

00:12:08.192 --> 00:12:12.192
"Hey, what's my life all about?" And you know, you need

00:12:12.032 --> 00:12:22.080
a really good spiritual director or confessor that will help you with this. And I don't mean someone that's going to tickle your ears and tell you what you want to hear. I mean someone that's really

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:24.000
really good and really clear.

00:12:24.064 --> 00:12:25.664
He will say.

00:12:26.176 --> 00:12:29.152
What is your life really about?

00:12:29.024 --> 00:12:30.688
Oh, it's about serving God.

00:12:30.816 --> 00:12:32.224
Really?

00:12:32.672 --> 00:12:39.040
I want an honest answer. I want a searching moral inventory of your life. What's it about?

00:12:38.944 --> 00:12:43.136
What do you get out of bed every morning in order to accomplish?

00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:44.064
Now,

00:12:43.744 --> 00:12:45.824
If we sinners are honest.

00:12:46.048 --> 00:12:53.568
We'll probably say some version of wealth or power or pleasure or honor or self-protection, you know?

00:12:53.568 --> 00:12:55.616
The old prideful self.

00:12:58.080 --> 00:13:02.464
Unless you're willing to take up your cross and your cross means

00:13:02.336 --> 00:13:04.640
Being stripped of all of that.

00:13:05.184 --> 00:13:15.232
Those aren't your ultimate goods. And all those weird twisted ways that the prideful self has used those things and manipulated others through them.

00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:15.968
through them and

00:13:15.776 --> 00:13:17.536
All of that

00:13:17.504 --> 00:13:19.456
you have to hate

00:13:21.024 --> 00:13:23.136
If you want to follow the Lord Jesus,

00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:25.024
Um.

00:13:25.216 --> 00:13:26.592
Hard stuff.

00:13:26.336 --> 00:13:27.392
Uh-huh.

00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:30.528
A cost of discipleship?

00:13:30.848 --> 00:13:32.032
You bet.

00:13:32.672 --> 00:13:42.144
You know, my generation got a lot of the kind of easy peasy spirituality, you know, God is love and just, you know, try to be kind and be a good person and,

00:13:42.176 --> 00:13:46.048
Well, yeah, I mean, nothing wrong with being a good person. I'm a little favored being a good person

00:13:45.984 --> 00:13:50.688
But that's the rudiments, everybody. That's the basis of the spiritual life.

00:13:51.264 --> 00:13:53.824
Serious stuff? Serious stuff? The high-octane stuff?

00:13:54.368 --> 00:13:56.672
Look at this Luke chapter 14.

00:13:56.928 --> 00:13:58.176
Unless you,

00:13:58.432 --> 00:14:04.224
Hate all these things unless you can put them in in a lower place.

00:14:04.288 --> 00:14:08.800
Unless you can affirm God as the supreme good in your life.

00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:12.480
You're not ready to follow the Lord.

00:14:12.928 --> 00:14:13.984
And so,

00:14:13.888 --> 00:14:17.696
You know, don't don't domesticate this, as I say, let the

00:14:17.216 --> 00:14:25.248
At the deep, deep challenge of these words, seep all the way down into your soul. I'm speaking to myself. I'm into my soul.

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:25.952
right?

00:14:27.648 --> 00:14:31.424
If we're serious about being disciples of the Lord Jesus,

00:14:31.808 --> 00:14:33.056
And God bless you.

00:14:36.800 --> 00:14:40.992
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

00:14:40.768 --> 00:14:46.336
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.
